list_ex_of_definition.ex_of_definition: He’s an experienced navigator of these seas.

list_ex_of_english: But these navigators were not putting their own financial well-being at risk from devoting time to scientific work.
The navigator steersman uses zigzag tacks to port and starboard across the wind in order to reach the intended point ahead.
So the navigator steersman judge must be alert at all times.
By explicitly modeling the effects of external features on the navigator, rather than the features themselves, generality is assured.
Real navigators are often good, but seldom optimal.
The navigator's most primitive craft could not weave new things and old referents into a coherent order.
The navigator will ensure that the ship sails in the right direction, so they have to engage with the engine room.
The navigator has been implemented on two mobile robots.
